title: Firki
subTitle: As a family decides to go for a drive, the father stays adamant on driving. His views on technology lead him to not trust navigational systems, but he himself struggles with directions.

title: Date Night
subTitle: A woman lovingly plans an elaborate date night for her husband. However, things go downhill when he is unable to make it.

title: Perks Of Being An Actor
subTitle: An ageing actor goes on a relentless pursuit to become a hero. But, soon these struggles land him in awkward situations.

title: Dadi Ka Murabba
subTitle: A young, simple village man looking to start a business and earn a name for himself is encouraged and supported by his grandmother to achieve his dream.

title: Duty
subTitle: Individuals from different walks of life and social classes demonstrate the interdependence of each social stratum on the other through their duties and responsibilities.

title: Exchange Offer
subTitle: Shiv lives alone, writing poetry on an old computer that breaks down. However, a service visit arranged by his son brings unexpected nostalgia, surprises and an intriguing exchange offer.

title: Dubki
subTitle: Dubki is a story based on a true incident of a female constable in male-dominated law enforcement. Despite being a tough and dominant constable at the Lalkurti police station, Ganga Yadav was troubled several times by SHO Durgesh Mishra. Ganga complained about it to the IPS officer and asked for a transfer; however, he refused to help her. The female constable was left with no other choice but to take justice into her own hands.

title: Dum Dum Deega Deega
subTitle: Ajju, the son of a drunkard beggar, lives on the streets of Mumbai but holds a positive outlook towards life. He refuses to beg and tries to earn money through respectable means.

title: Faboo
subTitle: Are we using social media to expand our horizon or are we overusing it and unknowingly desensitizing ourselves? Faboo explores this aspect of social media and nudges us to think about it through this story of a mother and son.

title: Destiny's Two
subTitle: A man newly married to a dwarf decides to go to a red-light area to fulfill his desire for a taller woman.

title: Game Of Caste
subTitle: Rakesh goes to his charming native village to visit his aunt, but soon discovers the underlying reality of discrimination among the various castes.

title: Electric Piya
subTitle: A light bulb falls in love with a human.

title: First Sin
subTitle: What would you do if you unexpectedly obtain magical powers? Ashwath, a failed businessman is having a troubled relationship with his wife. One fine morning he gets a Sand-timer at his doorstep. Life takes a turn when he discovers magical powers in it. Will the Sand-timer be a boon or curse?

title: Foul
subTitle: Against the setting of a journey to Thailand, Ayush, a lustful businessman, possesses both the capability and cleverness to be unfaithful to his wife and shatter her aspirations of moving to Canada. Yet, the question remains: Can he thwart her pursuit of realizing her dreams?

title: Cycle Of Sorrows
subTitle: Set in a rural village, this heart-wrenching story follows a poor father with a beloved daughter, who still yearns for a son as his pregnant wife prepares to give birth. Driven by financial hardship, he makes a tragic decision that not only shatters his family but leaves his relationship with his daughter and wife forever scarred. Watch this emotional tale of a father's regret and the lasting impact on his family. Can he undo the damage he's caused?

title: Expectations
subTitle: A boy struggles to grapple with his emotions because of expectations laid down by society and decides to take drastic measures.

title: Dwand
subTitle: Ruby, raised to believe in her potential, however, finds herself married to a traditional man, Vivek. After motherhood, she decides to pursue an advertising career, sparking unforeseen troubles.

title: #Goals
subTitle: After some time apart, Meera and Ranbir find their relationship at a point where it becomes a perfect example of the shallowness and fragility of modern-day dating.

title: Dawn To Dusk
subTitle: Nisha faces unimaginable pain as an orphan suffering from skin cancer. Though at peace with her reality, she discovers a glimmer of hope when she meets a young hospital worker named Suraj.

title: Best Friend
subTitle: A misunderstanding about his lover and friend propels Manav into a violent rage.

title: Bridge
subTitle: Widower Mukesh lives with son Rahul, 28. Rahul finds his father's behavior odd and Mukesh resents his son's constant judgment of his choices.

title: Beyond Failing
subTitle: A young student struggles with academic pressure due to poor performance. However, she sets out on a path of self-discovery and soon finds her true passion.

title: Bully
subTitle: A girl holds her brother hostage, however, she must confront the dark side of her life and face the harsh truths that threaten to break her.

title: Calling Bell
subTitle: A demented delivery man forces himself inside the house of a young lady, threatening to kill her. However, the confrontation takes an unusual turn when the true nature of his visit is revealed.

title: Black Coffee
subTitle: A woman faces sexual harassment at the hands of her boss. Later, she decides to teach him a lesson with the help of her colleague.

title: Bed Tea
subTitle: An unexpected tale of a rainy morning brings about a question about the existence of hidden evil behaviour in relationships.

title: Bepar
subTitle: On the surface, Indian immigrant Kritika and her Pakistani husband Faiz appear to be happily married. Underneath, however, their inter-faith union is caught in between love and cultural differences.

title: Choices
subTitle: Just one day before their wedding, Ritesh confesses something to Yami that threatens to change the course of their relationship.

title: Bhagwaan - The Faith
subTitle: A routine gym outing for three friends becomes a series of unusual interactions with diverse strangers. Their day reaches a pivotal moment when they cross paths with an enigmatic street dweller.

title: Bita Hua Pal
subTitle: The journey of a woman named Mira, who, like many others, finds herself questioning the foundation of her relationship. As she navigates the ups and downs of her own love story, she reflects on the nature of love and the challenges of maintaining a lasting connection.

title: Chashmadeed
subTitle: An ageing mother, living with her entitled son and his wife, finds her sight blurring and clearing like a malfunctioning camera lens one morning. Soon, a visit to a nearby eye clinic, strongly suggested by her young neighbour, leads to unexpected revelations.

title: Charitra Varnan
subTitle: A cab driver's kind attempt to help a weeping woman who dashed out of her house after a fight with her husband goes terribly wrong.

title: Anu Aur Di
subTitle: After a heated breakup, an angry girl calls her older sister for a late-night pickup. However, they soon get into a fight and are pulled over by the police.

title: Bahaar
subTitle: A young woman gets married, with the typical expectations of a blissful domestic life. However, her dreams turn into a nightmare when her mother-in-law constantly harasses and humiliates her solely because she has been unable to conceive after five years of marriage.

title: Aflatoon
subTitle: Two siblings dwelling in a distant land who yearn to transmit a sugary delicacy to their ailing patriarch. These brothers diligently arrange the dispatch of a confection to comfort their father during his recovery.

title: A Tale Of An Onion Witch Chapter 2
subTitle: A newlywed couple encounters a woman claiming to be Mangla, who cautions them about an ancient witch roaming the area at night in search of onions. However, the situation takes an unexpected turn when a young girl desperately seeks assistance by knocking on their door at the stroke of midnight, plunging the couple into a potentially perilous scenario.

title: Ruk Jana Nahi
subTitle: A withdrawn young man living with his father begins to regain purpose when a wedding next door brings people noise and quiet moments of unexpected hope.

title: Aakhri Kahani
subTitle: A desperate writer plans one final movie pitch to a producer. However, he ends up driving the producer in his taxi, giving him an unexpected opportunity to share his idea during the ride.

title: Baggage
subTitle: Sara's twin sister disappears in a bizarre manner, leaving her to deal with the loss. However, when she is unable to come to terms with it, Sara decides to find answers.

title: Baggage
subTitle: Sara's twin sister disappears in a bizarre manner, leaving her to deal with the loss. However, when she is unable to come to terms with it, Sara decides to find answers.

title: Adarniya Mantri Ji
subTitle: Finance Minister and her secretary seize black money, yet half goes missing. Later, the secretary reveals he's behind the theft as part of a secret plan. The story ends unresolved.

title: Abba Ki Chaddi
subTitle: A troubled housewife, weary and worn down by her husband's numerous past misdeeds, finally seeks the retribution she believes is long overdue.

title: Alvida
subTitle: A heartbroken man sits alone in a bar, haunted by the end of a relationship, and confronts the agonising necessity of saying a final goodbye.

title: Aam Ka Achaar
subTitle: Haunted by the riots that took his parents 20 years ago, Karan confronts the man who once loved him as a son-yet betrayed him in the worst way. Torn between revenge and forgiveness, he seeks meaning in the madness. A powerful story of loss, betrayal, and the fight for redemption.

title: Antahkaran
subTitle: A devout Hindu's quest for vengeance is complicated by his two friends with conflicting ideologies, both of whom attempt to manipulate his actions.

title: A Tale Of An Onion Witch
subTitle: Two flatmates hear about a witch who wanders around and asks for onions. However, they become shocked when the witch turns out to be an attractive woman instead.

title: Ahsaas
subTitle: After being rejected by their fathers, Raju and Anu elope and get settled in a village but when the parents learn about their whereabouts, they decide to bring them back.

title: Ansh: The Deadly Part
subTitle: An honest police officer dedicated to uprooting crime ruffles the feathers of corrupt politicians and criminals, who scheme to stop him.

title: Bahar Aa Chaman Prakash
subTitle: Bahar Aa Chaman Prakash delves into the story of a man reluctant to marry his lifelong acquaintance. Shutting himself away and avoiding his father, he faces the girl his father wishes him to wed. When she joins him and locks themselves in a room, they emerge with a revelation connected to the man's inner struggles. Will his father embrace this truth?

title: Adhure Poore Se Hum
subTitle: Two college time friends embark on a long drive on a Sunday morning, leaving their bustling city lives behind. As they amble through the hilly roads, they reveal to each other, their old longings and hidden pasts. Their rose-tinted nostalgia is broken, and they come face to face with their imperfect lives.

title: 10.30 Lets Go To School
subTitle: A determined village girl struggles to attend school as her family expects her to stay home, but her love for learning drives her to find clever ways to keep studying.

title: 23 B Raheja
subTitle: 23B Raheja is a gripping one-night drama that peels back the glossy layers of the entertainment industry to expose the shadows lurking beneath. The story revolves around a celebrated casting director whose charm masks a long trail of manipulation and exploitation. His power begins to crumble when a young woman arrives at his door, posing as an aspiring actress but with a haunting connection to his past. As the night unfolds, so does a tense game of revelations.
